An Ikeja Chief Magistrate’s Court on Monday remanded a 42-year-old man, Bola Isiaka, in Kirikiri Prison for allegedly defiling his neighbour’s daughter. <img class="size-full wp-image-1265514 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="Court remands Kano businessman over alleged N8.8m fraud" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Chief Magistrate, Mrs Olufunke Sule-Amzat did not take the defendant’s plea and ordered him to be remanded in prison until Nov. 14 for Director of Public prosecutions advise.(DPP) The defendant, a bus conductor, who resides at 16, Oremeta St., Iju Ishaga, Lagos is being tried for defilement. Earlier, the prosecutor, ASP Benson Emuerhi told the court that the offence was committed on Sept. 19 at the defendant’s residence. Emuerhi said that the complainant, a 10-year-old girl, lives with her parents in the same compound with the defendant. ”The defendant called her on the pretence of sending her on an errand, but he shut the door and defiled her,” he said. Emuerhi added that the girl told her mother and the accused was arrested. The offence according to the prosecutor contravened Section 137 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State,2015. Vanguard An Ikeja Chief Magistrate’s Court on Friday ordered the remand in prison custody of  a 34-year-old businessman, Charles Okpara, for allegedly defiling his 15-year-old neighbour’s daughter. May 31, 2019 In "News" An Ikeja Chief Magistrate's Court, yesterday, remanded a mechanic, Opeloyeru Yusuf, in Kirikiri Prison for allegedly defiling his neighbour’s 11-year-old daughter. April 27, 2016 In "News" An Ikeja Chief Magistrates' Court on Thursday remanded a 24-year-old man, Savior Edith to Kirikiri Prison for allegedly defiling his neighbour’s three-year-old daughter. March 31, 2016 In "News"